","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: habitational name from Ravenscroft (Cheshire), from the genitive case of an Old English personal name <i>Hræfn</i> (genitive <i>Hræfnes</i>, from Old English <i>hræfn</i> ‘raven’) + Old English <i>croft</i> ‘paddock, smallholding, enclosure’."],"variants":[{"name":"Ravencraft","meanings":["English: variant of   Ravenscroft  ."]},{"name":"Ravenscraft","meanings":["English: variant of   Ravenscroft  ."]}]},{"name":"Harry","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Pet form of   Henry .  This was the usual English form of <i>Henry</i> in the Middle Ages and later. It was used by  Shakespeare , for example, as the familiar name of the mature  King Henry V  (  compare  Hal  ). Since the publication of the first of  J. K. Rowling's  Harry Potter titles (Harry Potter and the Philosopher's Stone) in  1997 , <i>Harry</i> has become extremely popular as an independent given name."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705195,"age":12,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705197,"age":85,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Harry Ravenscroft was born in 1370, in Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England, his father, Ralph Ravenscroft, was 46 and his mother, Ravenscroft, was 41. He had at least 1 son with Catherine de Holand."},"et":{"1370–":"1370–Surnud","1370–Male":"1370–Surnud","1382–1430":"1382–1430","1395–1438":"1395–1438","1325–Male":"1325–Surnud","1330–Female":"1330–Surnud","1325":"1325","1455":"1455","1430":"1430","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1438":"1438","Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England":"Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England","Cotton End, Northamptonshire, England":"Cotton End, Northamptonshire, England"},"fi":{"1370–":"1370–Kuollut","1370–Male":"1370–Kuollut","1382–1430":"1382–1430","1395–1438":"1395–1438","1325–Male":"1325–Kuollut","1330–Female":"1330–Kuollut","1325":"1325","1455":"1455","1430":"1430","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1438":"1438","Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England":"Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England","Cotton End, Northamptonshire, England":"Cotton End, Northamptonshire, England"},"fr":{"1370–":"1370–Décédé","1370–Male":"1370–Décédé","1382–1430":"1382–1430","1395–1438":"1395–1438","1325–Male":"1325–Décédé","1330–Female":"1330–Décédée","1325":"1325","1455":"1455","1430":"1430","1330":"1330","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1370":"1370","1438":"1438","Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, England":"Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, Angleterre","Cotton End, Northamptonshire, England":"Cotton End, Northamptonshire, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Harry Ravenscroft est né en 1370, à Hardingstone, Northamptonshire, Angleterre, son père, Ralph Ravenscroft, avait 46 ans et sa mère, Ravenscroft, avait 41 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Catherine de Holand."},"de":{"1370–":"1370–Verstorben","1370–Male":"1370–Verstorben","1382–1430":"1382–1430","1395–1438":"1395–1438","1325–Male":"1325–Verstorben","1